    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">06</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Major Battles</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">The Siege of the Alamo: Heroism and Sacrifice</h2><ul><li>February-March 1836: Mexican forces besieged the Alamo mission in San Antonio</li><li>Texan defenders, including Davy Crockett and Jim Bowie, fought to the death</li><li>Became a rallying cry for Texan independence</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Alamo siege was a pivotal event where a small Texan force held out against a larger Mexican army, inspiring greater support for the revolution. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s21\">[21]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The phrase 'Remember the Alamo!' motivated Texan troops in later battles.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss how stories of sacrifice can influence public opinion.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing the Alamo only as a military defeat without its symbolic impact.</p></div></div>",
