    "num": "07",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">07</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Military Campaigns</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">The Goliad Campaign and Its Consequences</h2><ul><li>Mexican forces captured Texan troops at Goliad in March 1836</li><li>Over 300 Texan prisoners were executed in the Goliad Massacre</li><li>Increased Texan resolve to win independence</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Goliad Massacre was a tragic event that intensified Texan anger and determination, influencing the revolution’s final stages. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s21\">[21]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texan forces used the massacre as propaganda to rally support.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> How do acts of violence against prisoners affect conflicts?</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the massacre’s impact on Texan morale and recruitment.</p></div></div>",
