    "num": "08",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">08</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Decisive Victory</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">The Battle of San Jacinto: Securing Texas Independence</h2><ul><li>April 1836: Texan army led by Sam Houston defeated Santa Anna’s forces</li><li>Battle lasted just 18 minutes but was decisive</li><li>Santa Anna captured, leading to Texas independence</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Battle of San Jacinto was the turning point that ended the war and secured Texas as an independent republic. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s21\">[21]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Sam Houston’s surprise attack caught Mexican troops off guard, ensuring victory.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Why might a short battle have such a lasting impact?</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Underestimating the strategic planning behind the quick victory.</p></div></div>",
