    "eyebrow": "Political Perspectives",
    "num": "09",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">09</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Political Perspectives</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Diverse Loyalties Among Texans and Tejanos</h2><ul><li>Not all Texans supported independence; some remained loyal to Mexico</li><li>Tejanos were divided between supporting Mexico and the revolution</li><li>Internal divisions complicated the conflict</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The revolution was not a unified movement; differing loyalties among settlers and Tejanos influenced the course and nature of the war. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s21\">[21]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s22\">[22]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Some Tejanos fought alongside Mexican troops, while others joined Texan forces.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Consider reasons why people in the same region might support opposing sides.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming a single, unified Texan identity during the revolution.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide9\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following groups had divided loyalties during the Texas Revolution?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;Anglo-American settlers&quot;,&quot;Tejanos&quot;,&quot;Enslaved African Americans&quot;,&quot;All of the above&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:3,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;All these groups had complex and sometimes conflicting loyalties, reflecting the internal divisions during the revolution.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Analyze how Santa Anna&#39;s centralist policies influenced the outbreak of the Texas Revolution.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Response should explain the shift from federalism to centralism under Santa Anna, how this alienated Texan settlers, and contributed to political tensions leading to revolution. Use examples from primary sources or historical evidence.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Santa Anna&#39;s centralist policies replaced the 1824 Constitution&#39;s federalist system, reducing Texas&#39; autonomy. This angered settlers who valued local control, leading to resistance and eventually revolution.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Santa Anna&#39;s centralist policies reduced Texas autonomy and caused tensions&quot;,&quot;The shift from federalism to centralism upset Texan settlers&quot;,&quot;Centralist policies led to political conflict that sparked the revolution&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
