    "num": "11",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">11</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Declaration of Independence</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">The Texas Declaration of Independence: Key Points</h2><ul><li>Declared Texas independent from Mexico on March 2, 1836</li><li>Listed grievances against Mexican government and Santa Anna</li><li>Established the Republic of Texas and provisional government</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Declaration formalized Texas’ break from Mexico, articulating the settlers’ reasons and political goals. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s21\">[21]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Grievances included the repeal of the 1824 Constitution and denial of local rights.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify which grievances reflect political vs. social concerns.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing the Declaration as only a symbolic document without political weight.</p></div></div>",
