    "eyebrow": "Leadership",
    "num": "12",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">12</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Leadership</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Sam Houston and the Provisional Government</h2><ul><li>Sam Houston appointed commander of Texan forces</li><li>Led military campaigns culminating in San Jacinto victory</li><li>Helped establish provisional government and stabilize Texas</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Sam Houston’s leadership was crucial in uniting Texan forces and guiding the new republic through war and governance challenges. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s21\">[21]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Houston’s strategic retreat preserved Texan forces for the decisive battle at San Jacinto.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss qualities that made Houston an effective leader during the revolution.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking political as well as military roles of leaders.</p></div></div>",
