    "eyebrow": "Primary Sources",
    "num": "14",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">14</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Sources</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Government Records and Declarations</h2><ul><li>Official documents show legal and political steps taken</li><li>Reveal how Texans justified independence legally</li><li>Provide insight into provisional government formation</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Government records from the revolution period document the formal processes Texans used to declare independence and organize governance, reflecting their political intentions and legal reasoning. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s3\">[3]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The Texas Declaration of Independence outlines grievances against Mexico and asserts the right to self-governance.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze a section of the Declaration to identify key complaints against Mexican rule.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the legal language and focusing only on emotional rhetoric.</p></div></div>",
