    "eyebrow": "Primary Sources",
    "num": "15",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">15</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Sources</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Archival Collections and Historical Commissions</h2><ul><li>Archives preserve diverse documents from the revolution</li><li>Include letters, official records, and personal accounts</li><li>Enable cross-referencing to verify historical events</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Historical archives and commissions collect and maintain a wide range of primary sources that allow researchers to reconstruct the Texas Revolution’s events and perspectives. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s3\">[3]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The Texas State Library and Archives Commission holds documents that reveal both Texan and Mexican viewpoints.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Explore an archival summary and identify types of sources available for research.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Relying on a single source without corroboration from others.</p></div></div>",
