    "eyebrow": "Political Challenges",
    "num": "18",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">18</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Political Challenges</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Governance Issues in the Provisional Government</h2><ul><li>Struggled with limited resources and divided loyalties</li><li>Faced challenges in establishing law and order</li><li>Negotiated with foreign powers for recognition and support</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The provisional government had to manage a fragile political situation while conducting a war, balancing internal governance with external diplomacy. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s21\">[21]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Efforts to raise funds and troops were hampered by factional disputes and scarce resources.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify key governance challenges faced by the provisional government and propose solutions.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming the provisional government had full control and stability during the revolution.</p></div></div>",
