    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">19</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Document Analysis Workshop</h2><ul><li>Examine excerpts from letters and declarations</li><li>Identify author’s purpose and perspective</li><li>Evaluate reliability and bias</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Practicing document analysis helps learners develop skills to critically assess primary sources and understand historical viewpoints. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s3\">[3]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Compare a letter from a Texan leader with a Mexican government proclamation to identify contrasting narratives.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze provided excerpts and answer guided questions about content and bias.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Taking sources at face value without questioning context or purpose.</p></div></div>",
