    "id": "slide28",
    "eyebrow": "Outcomes and Legacy",
    "num": "28",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">28</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Outcomes and Legacy</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Political Consequences for Mexico</h2><ul><li>Loss of Texas weakened Mexican territorial control</li><li>Exposed weaknesses in Mexican government and military</li><li>Increased internal political instability in Mexico</li><li>Set precedent for future regional separatist movements</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Mexico’s loss of Texas was a significant blow to its territorial integrity and revealed internal challenges. The revolution contributed to political instability and inspired other regions to consider independence or autonomy. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s21\">[21]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Following Texas independence, Mexico faced further rebellions and struggled to maintain control over northern territories.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Evaluate how the Texas Revolution influenced Mexico’s political landscape in the 1830s and beyond.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Mexico quickly recovered from the loss of Texas without lasting effects.</p></div></div>",
