    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">31</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Application</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Simulating a Provisional Government Debate</h2><ul><li>Role-play key figures debating governance challenges</li><li>Discuss issues like law enforcement, defense, and diplomacy</li><li>Explore differing priorities among settlers and Tejanos</li><li>Practice negotiation and decision-making skills</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Simulating the provisional government meeting helps learners understand the practical difficulties of governing a new republic amid internal divisions and external threats. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s21\">[21]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Debate over how to allocate limited resources between military defense and civil administration.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> In your role, argue for your group’s priorities and seek compromise with others.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Oversimplifying the provisional government as unified and effective.</p></div></div>",
