    "eyebrow": "Transfer",
    "num": "32",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">32</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Transfer</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Comparing Texas Revolution Governance to Other Revolutions</h2><ul><li>Identify similarities with American and Mexican revolutions</li><li>Examine differences in political structures and challenges</li><li>Consider how context shapes revolutionary outcomes</li><li>Apply lessons from Texas to broader revolutionary studies</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Comparing the Texas Revolution’s governance with other revolutions deepens understanding of common patterns and unique factors influencing revolutionary success and state-building. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s21\">[21]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Unlike the U.S. Revolution, Texas struggled with international recognition and internal divisions during its provisional government phase.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Compare governance challenges in Texas with those in another revolution you know.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming all revolutions follow the same political trajectory.</p></div></div>",
