    "num": "34",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">34</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Essay Prompt: Analyzing the Texas Revolution’s Causes and Effects</h2><ul><li>Explain key political and social causes of the revolution</li><li>Describe major battles and their outcomes</li><li>Assess the revolution’s immediate and long-term impacts</li><li>Incorporate multiple perspectives and primary source evidence</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This essay task encourages learners to synthesize knowledge and practice historical argumentation using evidence from the lesson. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s3\">[3]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s21\">[21]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> An essay might argue that Santa Anna’s centralism triggered resistance, leading to battles like the Alamo, and resulting in Texas independence with lasting regional consequences.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Draft an outline for your essay addressing these points with supporting evidence.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Failing to support claims with specific examples or sources.</p></div></div>",
