    "eyebrow": "Practice",
    "num": "35",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">35</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Group Discussion: Perspectives on the Texas Revolution</h2><ul><li>Represent Anglo settlers, Tejanos, Mexican loyalists, and enslaved people</li><li>Discuss how the revolution affected your group</li><li>Explore conflicts and alliances among groups</li><li>Reflect on how perspectives shape historical narratives</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This group activity fosters empathy and critical thinking by exploring diverse experiences and viewpoints during the revolution. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s21\">[21]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s22\">[22]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Tejanos may express feelings of betrayal and loss, while Anglo settlers emphasize independence and opportunity.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Prepare and share your group’s perspective, then engage in respectful dialogue with others.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Stereotyping groups or ignoring internal diversity within groups.</p></div></div>",
