    "id": "slide36",
    "eyebrow": "Check Your Understanding",
    "num": "36",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">36</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Check Your Understanding</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Quiz: Causes, Battles, and Outcomes</h2><ul><li>What political change in Mexico triggered tensions with Texas settlers?</li><li>Name two major battles of the Texas Revolution and their significance.</li><li>Who were the key groups involved and what were their perspectives?</li><li>What were the immediate and long-term outcomes of the revolution?</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This quiz assesses learners’ grasp of essential facts and concepts covered so far, reinforcing retention and comprehension. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s21\">[21]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s22\">[22]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Answer: Santa Anna’s centralist policies; Battle of the Alamo (heroic defense), Battle of San Jacinto (decisive victory); Anglo settlers, Tejanos, Mexican loyalists; Texas independence and ongoing conflict.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Answer these questions in writing or discussion to check your understanding.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Confusing battles or oversimplifying group roles.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide36\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following groups had divided loyalties during the Texas Revolution?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;Anglo-American settlers&quot;,&quot;Tejanos&quot;,&quot;Enslaved African Americans&quot;,&quot;All of the above&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:3,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;All these groups had complex and sometimes conflicting loyalties, reflecting the internal divisions during the revolution.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Analyze how Santa Anna&#39;s centralist policies influenced the outbreak of the Texas Revolution.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Response should explain the shift from federalism to centralism under Santa Anna, how this alienated Texan settlers, and contributed to political tensions leading to revolution. Use examples from primary sources or historical evidence.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Santa Anna&#39;s centralist policies replaced the 1824 Constitution&#39;s federalist system, reducing Texas&#39; autonomy. This angered settlers who valued local control, leading to resistance and eventually revolution.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Santa Anna&#39;s centralist policies reduced Texas autonomy and caused tensions&quot;,&quot;The shift from federalism to centralism upset Texan settlers&quot;,&quot;Centralist policies led to political conflict that sparked the revolution&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
